729849f-a.title: Richmond: Victory Boulevard - Jewett Avenue
729849f-a.text:
Victory Boulevard, adjoining the N.E. corner of Jewett
Avenue. The maps from 1874 to 1907 show the house to have be-
longed to W. Kirk. It was owned by Jos. M. Hoffmann in 1917.
April 25, 1929
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
729849f-a.folder: Victory Boulevard & Jewett Avenue, Staten Island, NY

729886f-b.title: Richmond: Watchogue Road - Victory Boulevard
729886f-b.text:
(1)
Watchogue Road, west side, north of Victory Boulevard,
showing the Blake House, a colonial structure. It was, at one
time, inhabited by Daniel Blake, once police captain, who was a
grandson of William W. Blake, of Revolutionary times.
1924.
P. 1  L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
A distant view of the rear of the house, at a later date.
September 26, 1925.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
729886f-b.folder: Watchogue Road & Victory Boulevard, Staten Island, NY

729042f-b.text:

operated by the Richmond Iron Mining Company(Beers's 1874
map).
